This is the entrance to the Rumare Guild. It doesn't smell
as much of alcohol compared to downstairs... I should have
registered here.

\n<Commander>It's impossible to continue! The explosion at the
Adventurer's Guild earlier confirms the presence of a "high-
ranking" monster!

\n<Commander>The troops below are desperately engaged in battle, but
they're being pushed back. And now, even more powerful
monster reinforcements have arrived. There's not even a one
in ten thousand chance of victory!

\n<Commander>We're aware that there are still many residents alive.
However, it's only a matter of time...
\n<Commander>As of this moment, I declare that Driane has fallen!

\n<Commander>The gunpowder has already been set up! Mages! Unleash all
your magical power!! Barrier mages, prevent the spread to
Lumare with your barriers!!

\n<Commander>This is our only chance to wipe out the monsters!! Collapse
the cliff along with the barricades!! Bury them aliveeeee!!

\n<Count Noblesse>...(The high-ranking monsters, the coagulation crystals, the
slum problemall resolved at once. Could there be a more
efficient method?)

\n<Count Noblesse>(Some may condemn this as a cold-hearted decision. However,
the day will come when this will be hailed as the best
course of action. A victory for humanity, won upon the
precious sacrifices made.)

\n<Commander>It's impossible to continue! Given the explosion at the
Adventurer's Guild earlier, it's confirmed that there are
"executive class" monsters present!

\n<Commander>The forces below are desperately engaged in battle, but
they're being pushed back. And now, even more powerful
monster reinforcements have arrived. There's not even a one
in ten thousand chance of victory!

\n<Commander>We also know that there are still many residents alive.
However, it's only a matter of time...
\n<Commander>As of now, I declare that Driane has fallen!

\n<Commander>The gunpowder has already been set up! Magician squad!
Unleash all your magical power!! Barrier mages, prevent the
spread to Lumare with your barriers!!

\n<Commander>This is our only chance to wipe out the monsters!! Collapse
the cliff along with the ramparts!! Bury them aliveeeee!!

\n<Count Noblesse>...(With the executive class monsters, the coagulation
crystal, and the slum problem all taken care of at once,
could there be a more efficient method?)

\n<Count Noblesse>(Some may condemn this as a cold-hearted decision. However,
the day will come when this will be praised as the best
move. A victory for humanity, won on the noble sacrifices.)

\n<Count Noblesse>(Kukuku... Hahahahaha! Those detestable poor people, I'll
grant them an honorable death in the end! With this, my
position is unshakable!)

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>Report!! The gunpowder!! All the gunpowder is damp and
unusable!!
\n<Count Noblesse>What did you say!?

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>Even if we cause an explosion now, it won't be powerful
enough to collapse the cliff! We'll only lose the ramparts!

\n<Magician A>Whoa! What's this? The ground is all slimy! When did this
happen!?
\n<Magician B>Whoa, hey! Slip...! With this, I can't... cast spells...!!

\n<Commander>Abort the plan!! Abort!! Magician squad, stop chanting and
fall back! Abort!! Abort-!!!

\n<Adventurer A>I can't stand this anymore! Move aside! I'm going down to
fight! I don't care if I can't come back!!

\n<Soldier C>I'm against this plan too!! What noble sacrifice!? It makes
me sick!!

\n<Soldier D>I'm going to fight too!! Whether Driane or Lumare exists or
not!!

\n<Soldier E>Now is the time to fill the hole from 50 years ago!! Not
with dirt, but with our hearts!!!

\n<Soldier F>Who was that! Who just said something clever!? After this is
over, I'll treat you to a beer!! Men! Let's goooooo!!!
\n<Soldiers>Uooooooohhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh!!!!
\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>...(It was right to inform Mele-san.)

\n<Lumare Gatekeeper B>("Do not hate the people of Driane," I've kept your last
wish, my friend. Even though your wife is no longer human,
her heart is more human than anyone else's.)

\n<Mele>Fufu Did you see that? My love. You were the one who lit
the first fire. It's all right now.

\n<Mele>Besides, Katara is here. That child will surely save both
Driane and Lumare. I can tell.

\n<Soldier D>Hey!! A beastperson cat is climbing up here at an incredible
speed!! They're carrying something!!
\n<Soldier E>What's that huge gem!? It's glowing yellow!!

\n<Count Noblesse>Damn it...!!! Idiots!!! Don't bring the coagulation crystal
over here!!!

\n<Commander>Coagulation crystal? Count Noblesse, did you just say
coagulation crystal...? The one that's glowing yellow?
\n<Count Noblesse>Ah...

\n<Commander>I see, gunpowder and magicians. You've made quite the
arrangements. We'll have a detailed discussion about this
later.

\n<Commander>We've figured out the monsters' objective!! It's the
coagulation crystal!! But leave that to the beastperson from
earlier!! Trust them!! Go down and save as many people as
you can!!
\n<Mele>See

A lodging so delightful that you look forward to going to
bed, and with a breakfast so delicious that you look forward
to waking up! Please enjoy your stay and check in at the
reception

\n<Katara>...(A bed you can't sleep in, and a breakfast so awful it
makes you want to puke. It's a far cry from the inn below.)

\n<Magician>Greetings. Are you also staying at this inn? I stopped by on
my journey, and it turned out to be the most charming place
to stay.

\n<Magician>There's even a little hot spring in the back. It's not
natural, but a healing mage has dissolved magical power into
it, so your skin will be glowing

\n<Magician>The cuisine is also exquisite, with a focus on quality
ingredients. The beds are like sleeping on clouds, they even
give you a sense of floating.

\n<Katara>...(This person isn't bad at all. Yet, I'm getting the urge
to scratch them.)

This is the entrance to the Rumare Guild. It doesn't smell
as much of alcohol compared to downstairs... I should have
registered here instead.

\n<Magician>Good day. Are you also staying at this inn? I stopped by on
my journey, and this has been the most wonderful lodging.

\n<Magician>There's even a little hot spring out back. It's not natural,
but a healing mage has dissolved magical power into it, so
your skin will be glowing

\n<Magician>The food was also exquisite, with a focus on quality
ingredients. The bed felt like sleeping on clouds, giving a
sense of floating.

\n<Katara>...(This person isn't bad at all. Yet, I'm getting the urge
to scratch them.)

\n<Magician>Greetings. Are you also staying at this inn? I stopped by on
my journey, and this has been the most wonderful lodging
I've found.

\n<Magician>There's even a little hot spring in the back. It's not
natural, but a healing mage has dissolved magical power into
it, so it makes your skin silky smooth

\n<Magician>The food is also exquisite, with a focus on quality
ingredients. The bed felt like sleeping on clouds, giving a
sense of floating.

\n<Katara>...(This person isn't bad at all. Yet, I'm getting the urge
to scratch them.)

\n<Soldier>Are you one of the adventurers below? You may pass.
Adventurers are treated as "those who belong nowhere."
Basically, if there's a request, you can enter anywhere.

\n<Soldier>But that also means "you always have no allies." If there's
any inconvenience, we, the guards of Lumare, will thoroughly
eliminate you. Understood?

\n<Adventurer A>Oh, you're from that time! How are you? Did you come up here
for work today?

\n<Heavily-Armored Adventurer>Rumors of a cat beastman adventurer...? Ah, I know of them.
They're twins, right?

\n<Heavily-Armored Adventurer>Oh, that's you? Anyone else? Hmm... sorry, I can't think of
anyone.

\n<Longsword Adventurer>A strong cat beastperson...? Hmm, I do have someone in mind,
but... they're not an adventurer.

\n<Longsword Adventurer>There were rumors about a cat beastperson causing a ruckus
around the Oregano area. They were so out of control that a
subjugation request was even issued.

\n<Longsword Adventurer>They were shouting "Come out, strong ones!" while snapping
trees and beating up adventurers, causing quite the
commotion. I don't know if that situation was ever resolved.

\n<Katara>A subjugation request, huh? Hmm, that doesn't sound like my
sister. Thanks!

\n<Katara>Ah, that must be someone else then. Thank you very much.
(Please, let it be someone else!)
\n<Longsword Adventurer>I hope you find your sister.
